Determines whether SSL certificates presented by the FTPS server are validated to ensure that they are for the correct server. If enabled a connection is only established if the presented certificate contains the server's hostname as either the subject's common name, or in a DNS name in the SubjectAlternativeNames extension. If this is set to "Split multipart message", upon receipt of a supported multipart MIME message the parts will be split into individual Rhapsody messages. If set to "Split based on content", upon receipt of a supported multipart MIME message the parts will be split based on rules so some parts will become mesasge bodies and some parts will become message properties. Part with either (1) Header "Content-Disposition" with attachment (2) Header "Content-Disposition" has filename parameter or (3) Header "Content-Type" header that is not a "text" MIME type, will become indivdiual Rhapsody messages and other parts will become its message properties. If set to "No split", the MIME message will be sent as one Rhapsody message.
